y, Munster, Ireland":"Arragh More, County Tipperary, Irland","Arragh More, County Tipperary, Ireland":"Arragh More, County Tipperary, Irland","Ormond, Tipperary, Munster, Ireland":"Munster, Irland"},"nl":{"1410–":"1410–Overleden","1401–Male":"1401–Overleden","1440–Male":"1440–Overleden","1410–Female":"1410–Overleden","1401":"1401","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1440":"1440","Arragh More, Tipperary, Munster, Ireland":"Arragh More, County Tipperary, Ierland","Arragh More, County Tipperary, Ireland":"Arragh More, County Tipperary, Ierland","Ormond, Tipperary, Munster, Ireland":"Munster, Ierland"},"en":{"1410–":"1410–Deceased","1401–Male":"1401–Deceased","1440–Male":"1440–Deceased","1410–Female":"1410–Deceased","1401":"1401","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1440":"1440","Arragh More, Tipperary, Munster, Ireland":"Arragh More, County Tipperary, Ireland","Arragh More, County Tipperary, Ireland":"Arragh More, County Tipperary, Ireland","Ormond, Tipperary, Munster, Ireland":"Munster, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"O'Kennedy","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish and Scottish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Ceannéidigh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Ceannéidigh</i>’ (from <i>ceann</i> ‘head’ + <i>éidigh</i> ‘ugly’); or from the Scottish Gaelic <b>Mac Cinnèidigh</b>, consisting of <i>mac</i> ‘son’ with an equivalent name. Compare   Canaday  ,   Cannady  ,   Cannedy  ,   Kannady  , and   Kenedy  .","History: Kennedy ancestral lands are found both in Ireland and in Scotland, where the family's medieval ancestral seat is sited on the Ayrshire coast, facing the Irish Sea. — The great-grandparents of President John Fitzgerald Kennedy (1917–63) came to North America as immigrants from Ireland in the 1840s. His paternal great-grandparents were Patrick Kennedy (1823–58), born in Dunganstown, County Wexford, Ireland, and Bridget Murphy, who was born probably in Owenduff, County Wexford, Ireland <i>c.</i> 1827; they came to Boston, MA, in 1849. His maternal great-grandparents were Thomas Fitzgerald (1823–85), who was born in Bruff, County Limerick, Ireland, and Rose Anna Cox, who was born probably in Tomregan or Kinawley, County Cavan, Ireland, <i>c.</i> 1835; they came to Boston, MA, in 1857. — An early Scottish Kennedy forebear of a quite different family was British colonial official Archibald Kennedy (1685–1763), the son of Alexander Kennedy of Craigoch, who emigrated to NY <i>c.</i> 1710."],"variants":[{"name":"Canada","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canaday   and   Canida  .","Spanish (<b>Cañada</b>): topographic name from <i>cañada</i> ‘glen, valley’."]},{"name":"Cannady","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canady  ,   Cannaday  , and   Kannady  ."]},{"name":"Cannaday","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canaday  ."]},{"name":"Canedy","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Cannedy  ."]},{"name":"Cannedy","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canedy  ."]},{"name":"Canaday","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canada   and   Cannaday  ."]},{"name":"Canady","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canada  ,   Canaday  , and   Kanady  ."]},{"name":"Canida","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  ."]},{"name":"Kanady","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canady  ."]},{"name":"Kannady","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Cannady   and   Kanady  ."]}]},{"name":"Mor","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional name from <i>mór</i> ‘large, great’. This was the commonest of all girls’ names in late medieval Ireland, and has continued in use in both Ireland and Scotland to the present day."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mor O'Kennedy was born in 1410, in Munster, Ireland. She married Murrough O'Brien in 1430, in Arragh More, County Tipperary, Ireland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in Arragh More, County Tipperary, Ireland."},"et":{"1410–":"1410–Surnud","1401–Male":"1401–Surnud","1440–Male":"1440–Surnud","1410–Female":"1410–Surnud","1401":"1401","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1440":"1440","Arragh More, Tipperary, Munster, Ireland":"Arragh More, County Tipperary, Iirimaa","Arragh More, County Tipperary, Ireland":"Arragh More, County Tipperary, Iirimaa","Ormond, Tipperary, Munster, Ireland":"Munster, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"1410–":"1410–Kuollut","1401–Male":"1401–Kuollut","1440–Male":"1440–Kuollut","1410–Female":"1410–Kuollut","1401":"1401","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1440":"1440","Arragh More, Tipperary, Munster, Ireland":"Arragh More, County Tipperary, Irlanti","Arragh More, County Tipperary, Ireland":"Arragh More, County Tipperary, Irlanti","Ormond, Tipperary, Munster, Ireland":"Munster, Irlanti"},"fr":{"1410–":"1410–Décédée","1401–Male":"1401–Décédé","1440–Male":"1440–Décédé","1410–Female":"1410–Décédée","1401":"1401","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1440":"1440","Arragh More, Tipperary, Munster, Ireland":"Arragh More, County Tipperary, Irlande","Arragh More, County Tipperary, Ireland":"Arragh More, County Tipperary, Irlande","Ormond, Tipperary, Munster, Ireland":"Munster, Irlande","lifeSummary":"Mor O'Kennedy est née en 1410, à Munster, Irlande. Elle a épousé Murrough O'Brien en 1430, à Arragh More, County Tipperary, Irlande. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Elle est décédée à Arragh More, County Tipperary, Irlande."},"de":{"1410–":"1410–Verstorben","1401–Male":"1401–Verstorben","1440–Male":"1440–Verstorben","1410–Female":"1410–Verstorben","1401":"1401","1410":"1410","1430":"1430","1440":"1440","Arragh More, Tipperary, Munster, Ireland":"Arragh More, County Tipperary, Irland","Arragh More, County Tipperary, Ireland":"Arragh More, Coun